Files:
- plugins/slack-enterprise/src/tools/list-stars.ts (fix catch block)

Context:
The tool tries the enterprise `saved.list` endpoint first, then falls back to `stars.list`. The catch block around line 36 catches ALL errors:

```typescript
try {
  // Try saved.list (enterprise) first
  ...
} catch {
  // Fall through to stars.list
}
```

Fix: Re-throw errors that are not endpoint-not-found:
```typescript
try {
  // Try saved.list (enterprise) first
  ...
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof ToolError && (error.category === 'auth' || error.category === 'rate_limit')) {
    throw error;
  }
  // Fall through to stars.list for other errors (404, method not allowed, etc.)
}
```

Import ToolError from @opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk if not already imported.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the stars.list fallback logic
- Do NOT change the saved.list API call
